comment: Shumpert (CLE) sets the screen on Iguodala (GSW) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.

Iguodala (GSW) and James (CLE) briefly engage away from the ball.

Iguodala's (GSW) contact on James' (CLE) drive is incidental to his attempt to defend him.

Correctly called 24 second violation.

Barnes (GSW) sets the screen on Shumpert (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Thompson (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Green's (GSW) drive to the basket.
Green (GSW) establishes legal guarding position outside of the restricted area and cleanly blocks James' (CLE) driving layup attempt which results in a jump ball.
Green (GSW) grabs James' (CLE) shoulder and affects his ability to jump.
James (CLE) commits a violation when he catches the jump ball.
Curry (GSW) draws Smith (CLE) into the air towards him and he makes contact during the shot attempt. This is a shooting foul, even when contact is created by the offensive player.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Curry (GSW) was attempting a two point field goal when he was fouled by Smith (CLE) was upheld.
Iguodala (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) drive to the basket.

Iguodala (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends James' (CLE) drive down the lane.

Barnes (GSW) makes contact with Dellavedova's (CLE) body and head, and the contact affects his shot attempt.
Dellavedova (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Curry's (GSW) shot attempt.
